	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=380><span id=Scholar>Cubwynn</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>67 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>levels 7-12 are particularly difficult for an Enchanter, as you are physically weak and your pet is sub-par. Additionally, other classes don't know what you can do, and see you as being useless.<br><br>I highly recommend NOT soloing in dungeons - they are truly meant for groups. You WILL die, and you will die often!!<br><br>If you really want to do this, you'll have to learn how to battle with multiple MOBs. If you are fighting two MOBs, your strategy should be to put one of them OUT OF THE WAY. You have two choices: Mesmerize or Root. Both will put one MOB out of commission for a while, and will draw his friend right to you. Stand far enough away from your prey, cast Mezz/Root, then quickly target the incoming MOB and cast Tashan - it only has a 1 sec. casting time and you should be able to get it off.<br><br>If you find yourself being battered by two MOBs, STAND STILL, darnit, and cast Color Flux. Color Flux is a 4 sec stun. Root takes 2.5 seconds to cast. Therefore, when being pounded on by two MOBs, cast Color Flux, then immediately cast Root as soon as spell recovery time is met. Then BACK UP!!!! One of your prey will be rooted, effectively putting him out of the fight for a time.<br><br>You should be able to handle two MOBs if need be using these tactics. I would encourage you, however, to only venture in dungeons while grouped.<br><br>Good Luck!!<br><br>Cubwynn Payne<br>High Elven Enchanter of the 30th Mezz<br>Ordo Ursi Prismatus<br>Lanys T'vyl</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
