	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>All of these suggestions are wonderful but they are overlooking something that is very obvious to people that have played for a long time..in fact its so obvious you dont even think about it anymore.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>Your timeing is off..thats all.  You can guage the speed a mob hits by watching the chat scroll.  Once ya have a feel for how fast certain mobs hit you will always have it and will natural time other mobs.  <br><br>The trick is to be hitting your spell hotkey just as the mob is swinging.  The net result is you get hit ..Joe Blow begins to cast colorflux.  Suitable pause..spell goes off just before the mob has a chance to attack again.  You cant really be told how to do the timeing of spells.  But trust me..you will get it eventually.  It only helps 1-20ish..once mobs start Tripleing and Quading it wont matter since you can cast through most single mobs.  <br><br>Stick with it..you will get it.<br><br>As for hunting...I cant stress enough that enchanters should be hunting wisps at lvl 8-14.  You have the only pet that is capapb;le of hitting them without magic weapons being added at that level.  Your spells work just fine.  you will be oom every kill pretty much..but the exp and the loot are worth it.  Personally I do 8-14 at wisps selling everything but GLS.  When i have 4 full backpacks usually around lvl 11 I go bank then back to the island.  Then around lvl 14 you should have 8 full back packs of GLS.  turn them all in for alot of cash for your level and enough exp to put you very close to lvl 16.<br><br>Just my 2p</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
